data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
This wizard will help you to connect your Android device to this computer.
The first option is to connect your device over a WIFI connection. This is convenient because you do not need any cables. However this option is not available for all devices.
The second option is to connect your device using a USB cable. This option requires a driver for your device. Obtaining and installing this driver is different for each manufacturer.

data.name: labelX10.Text
data.value:
Before you can connect your device using USB to this computer, you must first enable USB debugging on your device.

To enable USB debugging follow these steps (on your device):

Step 1: Launch the Settings app.

Step 2: Select Applications

Step 3: Select Development

Step 4: Check USB Debugging

Now leave the settings app.
